            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p>
               <choice><orig>Μνημῖο<lb break="no"/>ν</orig><reg>μνημεῖον</reg></choice>
               <choice><orig>Γερμαν<lb break="no"/>ὸς</orig><reg>Γερμανοῦ</reg></choice>Μάρσου,<lb/>ἀποθανόν<lb break="no"/>τος ἐτῶν<lb/>
               <num value="25">κε</num> ἔτους
                        <num value="327">τ<lb break="no"/>κζ</num>, ἐν μηνὶ<lb/>
               <choice><orig>Ἀρτεμεσίου</orig><reg>Ἀρτεμισίῳ</reg></choice>
                    <lb/>
               <g type="cross"/>
               <num value="23">κγ</num>,
                            <expan><abbr>ἡμ</abbr><ex>έ</ex><abbr>ρ</abbr><ex>ᾳ</ex></expan>
                    <expan><abbr>Κ</abbr><ex>υρίο</ex><abbr>υ</abbr></expan>
                    <num value="6">ς</num>.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Monument of Germanus, (son) of Marsos, who died (at the age) of 25 years, (in
                    the) year 327, on the 23rd (day) of the month Artemisios, on the 6th day of
                    (the) Lord (Friday).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>This is one of the few cases, among the inscription of Zoora, in which the letter
                    comprising the year are splitted between two lines, likely due to miscalculation
                    of the available writing space.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
